      visual:`enum Day { MON, TUE, WED, THU, FRI, SAT, SUN }\n\nEnumMap internals: Object[] of length 7, indexed by ordinal\nEnumSet  internals: long bitmask (1 bit per constant)\n\nEnumMap<Day,String> plan;\nplan.put(Day.MON, "Standup");   // O(1) — array write\nplan.get(Day.FRI);              // O(1) — array read\n\nEnumSet<Day> weekend = EnumSet.of(Day.SAT, Day.SUN);\nEnumSet<Day> weekdays = EnumSet.complementOf(weekend);`,
      syntax:`EnumMap<EnumType, V> map = new EnumMap<>(EnumType.class);\nmap.put(EnumType.CONST, value);\n\nEnumSet<EnumType> set = EnumSet.of(EnumType.A, EnumType.B);\nEnumSet<EnumType> all  = EnumSet.allOf(EnumType.class);\nEnumSet<EnumType> none = EnumSet.noneOf(EnumType.class);`,
      code:`enum Day { MON, TUE, WED, THU, FRI, SAT, SUN }\n\nEnumMap<Day, String> plan = new EnumMap<>(Day.class);\nplan.put(Day.MON, "Standup");\nplan.put(Day.WED, "Code Review");\nplan.put(Day.FRI, "Deployment");\nSystem.out.println(plan.get(Day.WED));  // Code Review\nSystem.out.println(plan.size());        // 3\n\nEnumSet<Day> weekend  = EnumSet.of(Day.SAT, Day.SUN);\nEnumSet<Day> weekdays = EnumSet.complementOf(weekend);\nSystem.out.println(weekend);   // [SAT, SUN]\nSystem.out.println(weekdays);  // [MON, TUE, WED, THU, FRI]\n\nSystem.out.println(weekend.contains(Day.SAT)); // true`,
